218
00:21:46.750 --> 00:22:07.639
Kostadis Roussos: The Bahamutian School answers, a universe in which divine providence prevails. Bahamut moved his pieces beforehand. The dragons obeyed because they were agents of a just god. The mortals, Stroud included, served as instruments of providence. By this reading, choice was real, but not sovereign. Stroud chose what he was fitted to choose.

219
00:22:07.640 --> 00:22:10.120
Kostadis Roussos: The chain was an arranged chain.

220
00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:11.810
Kostadis Roussos: Providence prevails.

221
00:22:14.790 --> 00:22:21.540
Ben Pfaff: I cannot put my finger on it, but I feel, I feel there must be a fallacy.

222
00:22:21.540 --> 00:22:25.390
Kostadis Roussos: Well, there's a third school of thought that perhaps your friend,

223
00:22:25.720 --> 00:22:27.560
