226
00:22:43.120 --> 00:23:00.020
Kostadis Roussos: Can remember some. Because the Dragon School answers, most quietly, a universe in which ancient agency rules, and mortals operate in the frames the Dragon Set. Protenthor chose to honor Stroud's move because Protanther is honorable, not because Bahamut compelled him.

227
00:23:00.020 --> 00:23:09.929
Kostadis Roussos: The metallic dragons followed Protanther because they trust their elders, not because the gods commanded them. The choosing is real, but the scope of the choosing is what the dragons permit.

228
00:23:09.990 --> 00:23:25.979
Kostadis Roussos: Three answers, three universes. They cannot be all right at the same time, and the question, Brother Grygum, matters in a way I've never seen a question rather. Because if the Stroud School is right, the gods are constrained, and the central truth of the cosmos is the irreducible mortal choice.

229
00:23:25.980 --> 00:23:44.259
Kostadis Roussos: That no power above or below can possess. The good gods cannot manufacture our mercy. The evil gods cannot manufacture our cruelty. There is no procedure that produces the human outcome reliably, because the human is not a stone or a star or a level, or a lever, and refuses when every calculation says they should obey.

230
00:23:44.520 --> 00:23:47.360
Ben Pfaff: But… but what if there's a fourth?

231
00:23:48.630 --> 00:24:04.980
