Kostadis Roussos: On the way, you pass a gray cat sleeping in the middle of the stairs. The feline remains motionless as you approach, but her yellow eyes open, daring anyone to disturb her. Bookwyrm steps gingerly around here.

733
01:06:27.180 --> 01:06:27.700
Kostadis Roussos: So…

734
01:06:27.700 --> 01:06:32.420
Thorin (Joe): I want to ask Bookwyrm about the cat. What… why is every… why did he step around the cat?

735
01:06:33.640 --> 01:06:38.020
Kostadis Roussos: He pauses and says, Nobody knows, but there's a theory about the cat.

736
01:06:39.080 --> 01:06:41.570
Thorin (Joe): What's the theory? Does a cat murder people?

737
01:06:42.590 --> 01:06:47.540
Kostadis Roussos: No, no, no, no, no, the concern is the cat is some kind of power that lives here.

738
01:06:48.910 --> 01:06:57.870
Kostadis Roussos: Nobody has been able to conclusively prove that it is, and nobody has been able to prove that it conclusively is not. And so, the cat stays where the cat wishes.

739
01:06:59.680 --> 01:07:01.299
Daz: That's kind of how cats always are, I think.

740
01:07:01.300 --> 01:07:02.529
Thorin (Joe): I mean, yeah, they don't listen anymore.

741
01:07:02.530 --> 01:07:04.000
Kostadis Roussos: bang.

742
01:07:06.650 --> 01:07:18.739
Kostadis Roussos: Actually, Fembris goes… turns to you and goes, oh my god, these avowed? Like, that's what cats do. Like, cats just sit wherever they want, and, like, these guys have turned it into an intergalact… interstellar, interspatial, interdimensional horror.

743
01:07:18.740 --> 01:07:25.129
Thorin (Joe): I mean, the cat could be some sort of familiar for somebody, or some sort of, you know, shapeshifter. We are, you know…

744
01:07:25.320 --> 01:07:28.940
Thorin (Joe): have to be open to every idea here. Are you saying that that's not the case?

745
01:07:28.940 --> 01:07:34.050
Kostadis Roussos: I'm just saying, they always… That's what they're always saying, it's just a cat.

746
01:07:35.320 --> 01:07:36.290
Gabe: Is it?

747
01:07:37.970 --> 01:07:43.470
Kostadis Roussos: Now he's… now he… you deliver that with such… Such emphasis!

748
01:07:43.960 --> 01:07:45.100
Kostadis Roussos: That is going.

749
01:07:45.580 --> 01:07:49.619
Kostadis Roussos: You know, if Booker was scared of the cat, maybe I should be scared of the cat.

750
01:07:51.550 --> 01:07:52.120
Kostadis Roussos: Right.

751
01:07:52.860 --> 01:08:03.409
Kostadis Roussos: You arrive at the crime scene. A solemn-faced watcher named Tadric guards the door to the chambers, and the bookworm shows up, and he defers to her immediately.

752
01:08:04.190 --> 01:08:13.510
Kostadis Roussos: bookform informs the Tadric that Kalan has been relieved from the investigation, and asked to focus intentions elsewhere.

753
01:08:14.080 --> 01:08:17.500
Kostadis Roussos: And she then says, these four will be taking over.

754
01:08:17.859 --> 01:08:29.419
Kostadis Roussos: And then she turns, she goes, and I must deal with other business. You are to report back to me as soon as you are done, and remove nothing from the room.

755
01:08:30.859 --> 01:08:32.850
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, so there's Tadric.

756
01:08:33.000 --> 01:08:38.550
Kostadis Roussos: He's a short, human male, 23 years old, with a dark brown haircut shaped like an upside-down bowl.

757
01:08:41.279 --> 01:08:42.669
Daz: Upside down. Oh.

758
01:08:42.830 --> 01:08:43.610
Kostadis Roussos: you know, like…

759
01:08:44.710 --> 01:08:49.039
Thorin (Joe): The traditional bowl cut. Or wait, no, does it actually… is it right side up?

760
01:08:49.520 --> 01:08:51.299
Kostadis Roussos: Upside down, so it's down like that, right?

761
01:08:51.300 --> 01:08:51.850
Thorin (Joe): Yeah, okay.

762
01:08:51.859 --> 01:08:52.289
Daz: Okay.

763
01:08:52.290 --> 01:08:53.420
Kostadis Roussos: It's like, you know…

764
01:08:55.990 --> 01:08:57.799
Thorin (Joe): His mom put a bowl on his head and then cut around the.

765
01:08:57.800 --> 01:08:59.100
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, exactly.

766
01:08:59.109 --> 01:09:00.299
Gabe: It's a walker.

767
01:09:00.300 --> 01:09:01.820
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, yeah, sorry, I, I…

768
01:09:02.250 --> 01:09:07.389
Kostadis Roussos: Or is it an upside… yeah, upside-down bowl. I was just thinking upside-down bowl, but I was thinking the bowl upside-down.

769
01:09:07.399 --> 01:09:10.729
Thorin (Joe): I know, you assumed that the ball went on… I mean, you know, I get where you came from.

770
01:09:10.729 --> 01:09:18.209
Kostadis Roussos: Like, I got confused. I'm like, an upside-down bowl cut. So the bowl cut is like this, and then I'm like, oh no, that's the upside down…

771
01:09:18.720 --> 01:09:20.080
Thorin (Joe): Alright, what's this dude's role?

772
01:09:24.260 --> 01:09:25.240
Thorin (Joe): What's his name?

773
01:09:25.500 --> 01:09:26.279
Kostadis Roussos: Tadric.

774
01:09:26.430 --> 01:09:28.350
Thorin (Joe): Tadric, I was thinking Tadric.

775
01:09:33.720 --> 01:09:38.980
Kostadis Roussos: So, let me just tell you, he, he was… you… what was your question again? Sorry.

776
01:09:40.590 --> 01:09:41.160
Kostadis Roussos: Joe.

777
01:09:41.160 --> 01:09:43.200
Thorin (Joe): I said, what's his role? What's his job?

778
01:09:44.880 --> 01:09:45.850
Thorin (Joe): Why is he here?

779
01:09:47.060 --> 01:09:49.019
Thorin (Joe): Contaminating our own crime scene.

780
01:09:49.020 --> 01:09:59.049
Kostadis Roussos: Well, he goes, I arrived at the crime scene with the gate warden around 8 this morning, after speaking briefly with A'lai, that's the guy who…

781
01:09:59.210 --> 01:10:12.350
Kostadis Roussos: was very excited about you guys solving this murder mystery as quickly as possible, because, you know, he felt that some… that, you know, somebody had to be voted into, you know, wants the government of Candlekeep to start functioning again, get past the whole murder thing.

782
01:10:12.430 --> 01:10:22.260
Kostadis Roussos: and Miss Hollypocket, and making a brief inspection of the scene, but the gate warden left to oversee the deployment of additional watchers during a newly declared state of emergency.

783
01:10:24.170 --> 01:10:26.270
Thorin (Joe): Was the state of the emergency due to the murder?

784
01:10:27.460 --> 01:10:29.250
Kostadis Roussos: Y-yes.

785
01:10:29.580 --> 01:10:33.129
Thorin (Joe): Okay, there might be another emergency we're not aware of, I'm just asking.

786
01:10:33.130 --> 01:10:39.610
Kostadis Roussos: Right. I mean, you know, one thing that pops into your head is you can ask about, you know, who else came by, when.

787
01:10:39.610 --> 01:10:48.030
Thorin (Joe): Yeah, I'm wondering, like, what is the timeline? Who found them? Has anybody actually left the crime scene since they were found? Like, what is the timeline here that we want to establish?

788
01:10:48.030 --> 01:11:02.459
Kostadis Roussos: Well, he goes… he turns to you and says, wow, that's a… that's a really good question. Janussi was found dead by great reader A'lai Aivenmore and the servant, Miss Hollypocket, around 7.30 in the morning, and the two of them raised the alarm.

789
01:11:04.070 --> 01:11:05.030
Kostadis Roussos: Alright.

790
01:11:06.410 --> 01:11:10.800
Thorin (Joe): Did they discover… did they discover him together, or did somebody discover him first? Do we know?

791
01:11:12.970 --> 01:11:18.530
Kostadis Roussos: I arrived at the crime scene with the gate warden around 8 AM, so for all I know, yes, they did.

792
01:11:18.890 --> 01:11:19.410
Kostadis Roussos: Okay.

793
01:11:19.410 --> 01:11:20.710
Thorin (Joe): So we're gonna have to interview them.

794
01:11:21.410 --> 01:11:30.679
Kostadis Roussos: Yes. Then a little bit later, Kazryn Nyantani arrived distraught and weeply, shortly after 8 AM, wanting to see the body of Janussi.

795
01:11:31.140 --> 01:11:33.550
Kostadis Roussos: Which she did, but only from the doorway.

796
01:11:33.660 --> 01:11:44.090
Kostadis Roussos: Then, Fheminor Scrivenbark stern up at 8.30, appearing shocked. She wanted to inspect the chamber, but it was… rules had already been set, nobody was allowed to go in.

797
01:11:45.440 --> 01:11:59.939
Kostadis Roussos: Then Bookward showed up at 9 from the baths, having been alerted to the situation. As Acting Head of Candlekeep, she was allowed to enter the chamber, but took a brief only look at the scene before confirming the garden warden's order not to admit anyone.

798
01:12:01.270 --> 01:12:12.549
Kostadis Roussos: And the gate warden returned at 11 to make a full investigation. He seemed careful not to sully the crime scene in any way before he left to make his report to the Council of Great Readers.

799
01:12:13.730 --> 01:12:14.779
Kostadis Roussos: He looks at you.

800
01:12:15.260 --> 01:12:17.859
Kostadis Roussos: Where is… what happened with the gate warden?

801
01:12:19.650 --> 01:12:21.750
Kostadis Roussos: He's the guy that got fired so that you can have the job.

802
01:12:21.750 --> 01:12:25.410
Thorin (Joe): Yeah, I mean, like, I don't know, they just asked us to step in, and we don't have any.

803
01:12:25.920 --> 01:12:29.550
Daz: We're, we're, we're just… we're trying to figure out what happened.

804
01:12:30.570 --> 01:12:39.929
Kostadis Roussos: Okay. Gatewarden's a great guy, you know, he's a really honest, he's a really stand-up guy. I don't know why they wouldn't want to have him do this investigation.

805
01:12:40.410 --> 01:12:48.910
Kostadis Roussos: Oh, well, well, he went inside and looked around and then left. He didn't tell me of any… that… he didn't share with me anything that he figured out.

806
01:12:50.590 --> 01:12:52.730
Thorin (Joe): Did it look like he discovered something?

807
01:12:55.050 --> 01:12:58.190
Kostadis Roussos: Tedrick thinks about it for a second.

808
01:12:59.070 --> 01:13:02.469
Kostadis Roussos: He definitely looked more determined after he walked out.

809
01:13:05.480 --> 01:13:16.369
Kostadis Roussos: So there… I don't know, though, look, I haven't looked inside. I'm not, you know, I'm… I've been standing outside and pausing and goes, I don't really like murder, blood scenes, kind of gross.

810
01:13:18.240 --> 01:13:20.529
Gabe: Did he touch anything whatsoever?

811
01:13:22.910 --> 01:13:26.279
Kostadis Roussos: Well, he seemed careful not to sully the crime scene.

812
01:13:28.320 --> 01:13:31.299
Gabe: Granted, but did you touch anything whatsoever?

813
01:13:32.470 --> 01:13:34.550
Kostadis Roussos: Not that I noticed.

814
01:13:36.090 --> 01:13:37.950
Gabe: Were you watching carefully?

815
01:13:37.950 --> 01:13:42.149
Kostadis Roussos: No, my job was to make sure nobody came in, not so much to look inside.

816
01:13:42.290 --> 01:13:43.080
Gabe: So you don't.

817
01:13:43.080 --> 01:13:44.420
Kostadis Roussos: No.

818
01:13:44.750 --> 01:13:51.779
Kostadis Roussos: I don't know, I, I, you know, that was… my job was, you know, my job was out here, crowd control.

819
01:13:52.710 --> 01:13:58.799
Kostadis Roussos: Make sure only the right people come in and out. You know, we don't want everybody coming in and out, and in and out, and in and out, and in and out.

820
01:14:00.290 --> 01:14:11.840
Kostadis Roussos: You know, like, Bookwyrm, and the Gatewarden, and… Janussi, and Kazryn, and… I don't think I did a good job. Did I do a good job?

821
01:14:13.470 --> 01:14:14.670
Kostadis Roussos: Alright.

822
01:14:14.770 --> 01:14:28.840
Kostadis Roussos: Okay, finally you're… he opens the door, and you're ready to enter the keeper's quarters. You enter a spacious, circular chamber, ringed by a dozen lancet windows that fill the room with natural light, which is made hazy by a thin.

823
01:14:29.050 --> 01:14:30.860
Kostadis Roussos: Bug of tobacco.

824
01:14:30.930 --> 01:14:38.890
Kostadis Roussos: Lying on the ground near the foot of the chamber's elegant mahogany desk in the center of the room is the corpse of a human male around 70 years old.

825
01:14:38.910 --> 01:14:52.269
Kostadis Roussos: His vacant eyes fixed on the ceiling, his splendid, flowing white robes are extremely bloodied around the torso, while a closer look reveals that his rib cage has been caved in and there is a gaping hollow in the chest.

826
01:14:54.950 --> 01:15:05.339
Kostadis Roussos: The wrist of the chamber is in some disorder. A chair has been toppled over near the desk. The desk itself is neatly arranged, with a single book lying open in the center, next to a pile of books on the left.

827
01:15:05.340 --> 01:15:15.269
Kostadis Roussos: and a stack of notes on the right. But the extinguished candles of the candelabra have burned down to their stub, leaving a waxy mess spilled below them, and an ink pot has been filled.

828
01:15:15.830 --> 01:15:32.139
Kostadis Roussos: On either side of the room, on the other side of the room, and to the desk, a marble statue and its pedestal lie on the ground. Blue gemstones appear to have been scattered on the stone floor in front of the safe, along with several empty pouches. A wooden set of stairs leads up to the second floor.

829
01:15:34.340 --> 01:15:41.570
Thorin (Joe): So it looks like a robbery, like somebody raided the safe, and what they were looking for is more valuable than blue gemstones?

830
01:15:41.570 --> 01:15:51.399
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, after they enter the chamber… Fembris, at this point in time, takes one look at the body, runs to one of the windows, flings it open, and starts vomiting outside of the tower.

831
01:15:51.820 --> 01:15:52.500
Daz: Oh, wow.

832
01:15:55.010 --> 01:15:56.039
Thorin (Joe): But who does that?

833
01:15:56.040 --> 01:15:58.819
Kostadis Roussos: Fembris, Fembris, your, your, your assistant.

834
01:15:58.820 --> 01:16:00.000
Thorin (Joe): Okay.

835
01:16:00.000 --> 01:16:01.580
Kostadis Roussos: you know.

836
01:16:01.980 --> 01:16:11.460
Kostadis Roussos: A gush of wind flows in. Fortunately, his vomit does not also flow in. Nothing disturbs the evidence. He decides, I… I need to… he needs to be…

837
01:16:11.680 --> 01:16:13.639
Kostadis Roussos: To go outside. Alright.

838
01:16:14.870 --> 01:16:19.350
Kostadis Roussos: So, there's a bunch of stuff you can investigate. Here, I'll just drop it into the chat so you can…

839
01:16:19.500 --> 01:16:21.430
Kostadis Roussos: Decide what you want to look in what order.

840
01:16:22.330 --> 01:16:27.189
Thorin (Joe): I feel like we need to, like, include where you have the list of suspects, and then where they were and everything, right?

841
01:16:27.190 --> 01:16:30.029
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, I'll get that list for you guys.

842
01:16:30.760 --> 01:16:33.510
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, I will… if you ever want to ask who was so…

843
01:16:34.130 --> 01:16:37.210
Thorin (Joe): There's just a lot of characters, and I'm not quite sure who's.

844
01:16:39.300 --> 01:16:52.760
Kostadis Roussos: Don't worry about the characters right now. Now you're doing the investigation of the crime scene. When it comes to… you will get a chance to meet with the characters, so focus… focus on the… focus on the room for the moment. Does that make sense?

845
01:16:52.910 --> 01:16:53.230
Thorin (Joe): Yeah.

846
01:16:53.230 --> 01:16:54.100
Daz: Yeah.

847
01:16:55.460 --> 01:16:57.030
Thorin (Joe): So what is… is there…

848
01:16:58.280 --> 01:17:02.840
Thorin (Joe): a source for the tobacco that we can see, because I would have expected… like, what time is it now?

849
01:17:03.210 --> 01:17:05.909
Kostadis Roussos: It's after 11, because, that's…

850
01:17:05.910 --> 01:17:09.810
Thorin (Joe): What happened between 7.30 and 11, where the tobacco smoke is still here?

851
01:17:10.350 --> 01:17:12.090
Kostadis Roussos: That I do not know.

852
01:17:16.010 --> 01:17:26.820
Kostadis Roussos: Hold on. I have to be honest with you guys. The Montreal Canadiens are playing the Buffalo Sabres in Game 7, and so I'm… my phone is being buzzed by my friends, so I had to check what happened.

853
01:17:29.550 --> 01:17:39.559
Kostadis Roussos: I've got two sets of friends, ones who are hoping for Buffalo, and another who are hoping for Montreal, so I don't know… whenever I get a, I don't know whether it's a, haha, good news.

854
01:17:41.310 --> 01:17:44.630
Kostadis Roussos: But Grygum tentatively agrees with the claim. Okay.

855
01:17:46.150 --> 01:17:47.900
Thorin (Joe): I lean over and feel for a pulse.

856
01:17:50.110 --> 01:17:56.850
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, so… do you, alright.

857
01:18:01.580 --> 01:18:04.480
Thorin (Joe): Alright, what's the book that's open in the center on the table?

858
01:18:04.850 --> 01:18:11.119
Daz: Yeah, we gotta check that out. And then also, can we look inside those bags and tell what might have been in the bags, the empty ones?

859
01:18:12.390 --> 01:18:15.009
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, so let's start with the desk, shall we?

860
01:18:15.200 --> 01:18:15.880
Daz: Yes.

861
01:18:16.320 --> 01:18:27.630
Kostadis Roussos: Piled on the left, on different… among the title… okay, so no investigation is required to search the desk, which are several books piled up on the left… left on discrete topics. Among the titles are…

862
01:18:28.470 --> 01:18:31.190
Kostadis Roussos: I will just, instead of trying to pronounce them…

863
01:18:35.280 --> 01:18:36.729
Kostadis Roussos: Why do you do this to me?

864
01:18:52.040 --> 01:18:56.929
Kostadis Roussos: Sorry, I clicked the button, and it, like, completely

865
01:18:57.150 --> 01:18:58.839
Kostadis Roussos: Took me to the wrong place. Alright.

866
01:19:04.120 --> 01:19:08.379
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, in the middle of the desk is a spell book entitled The Discoveries.

867
01:19:10.260 --> 01:19:16.700
Kostadis Roussos: And behind the book is a seven-armed bronze candelabra, its candles all burned to the stub.

868
01:19:16.880 --> 01:19:17.660
Kostadis Roussos: Alright.

869
01:19:19.710 --> 01:19:21.279
Kostadis Roussos: So, let me just put that down.

870
01:19:24.900 --> 01:19:28.720
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, hold on, I need to, do something. This is actually starting to get on my nerves.

871
01:19:36.180 --> 01:19:38.350
Kostadis Roussos: I hope you, sorry.

872
01:19:38.350 --> 01:19:40.400
Thorin (Joe): What page is the book open to?

873
01:19:41.020 --> 01:19:43.630
Kostadis Roussos: Amazing.

874
01:19:43.670 --> 01:19:44.610
Thorin (Joe): Spell.

875
01:19:46.060 --> 01:19:46.670
Kostadis Roussos: Alright.

876
01:19:49.640 --> 01:19:51.210
Kostadis Roussos: Alright,

877
01:19:58.710 --> 01:20:00.379
Kostadis Roussos: Let's see where it says, straight through.

878
01:20:02.520 --> 01:20:03.250
Kostadis Roussos: Word.

879
01:20:05.910 --> 01:20:06.700
Kostadis Roussos: Skilled.

880
01:20:08.840 --> 01:20:11.450
Kostadis Roussos: Let's go… This is…

881
01:20:11.810 --> 01:20:19.929
Daz: And I want to check the notes, too. It said there was a pile of notes on the side. Can we… can we infer, like, what he was trying to figure out from the book, or was it just…

882
01:20:20.140 --> 01:20:21.320
Kostadis Roussos: Yeah, no, absolutely.

883
01:20:21.320 --> 01:20:23.430
Daz: Academic stuff, like, what was going on?

884
01:20:23.650 --> 01:20:25.060
Kostadis Roussos: Yep, yep, yep, yep, yep.

885
01:20:25.240 --> 01:20:26.060
Kostadis Roussos: Alright.

886
01:20:27.120 --> 01:20:29.479
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, fine. Finally got to the,

887
01:20:30.130 --> 01:20:36.370
Kostadis Roussos: There's something that won't keep clicking away at me. Alright, so you're looking at the desk.

888
01:20:36.470 --> 01:20:43.849
Kostadis Roussos: Alright, to the right of the discoveries lies a single sheath leaf of papyrus with the book's title.

889
01:20:44.220 --> 01:20:52.990
Kostadis Roussos: Written in common, which… with notes written in Celestial. The notes are musing on the unfamiliar spells and the discoveries and how they might be cast.

890
01:20:55.160 --> 01:21:00.840
Kostadis Roussos: So, it looks like just generic scientific research by some… by an academic.

891
01:21:01.860 --> 01:21:05.139
Kostadis Roussos: You also notice a quill on the floor by the desk.

892
01:21:05.380 --> 01:21:08.600
Kostadis Roussos: Its nib covered in midnight blue ink.

893
01:21:10.630 --> 01:21:21.979
Kostadis Roussos: Also on the floor by the desk is a wicker basket with a single discarded linen ink carry in it. The inside of the linen carrier is slightly damp, and was clearly the vessel…

894
01:21:22.240 --> 01:21:24.100
Kostadis Roussos: of the Midnight Blue Ink.

895
01:21:27.600 --> 01:21:29.720
Thorin (Joe): Well, it said that there was ink spilled

896
01:21:30.170 --> 01:21:33.239
Thorin (Joe): Ink pot had been spilled. Is that the ink pot that was spilled?

897
01:21:33.460 --> 01:21:34.120
Kostadis Roussos: Yes.

898
01:21:34.330 --> 01:21:34.960
Thorin (Joe): Okay.

899
01:21:36.310 --> 01:21:42.529
Kostadis Roussos: Finally, at the back of the desk, on the right, is a large pile of… here, I'm just gonna cut and paste this so you have this.

900
01:21:44.860 --> 01:21:45.650
Kostadis Roussos: Right?

901
01:21:50.960 --> 01:21:51.710
Kostadis Roussos: Okay.

